      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 3,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "String-based selector APIs for runtime paths introduce brittle control flow and hidden invalid-state behavior.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "low_level_elegance",
        "related_files": [
          "goseg/defaults/defaults.go",
          "goseg/config/runtimecontext/context.go"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`DockerData(pathType string)` checks `pathType == \"volumes\"` and uses an implicit else branch for all other values.",
          "Callers use literal selector strings (`\"basePath\"` and `\"volumes\"`), so typo or drift changes behavior silently rather than failing fast.",
          "`dockerDirDefault` in runtime context builds on this selector and appends `/`, coupling low-level path correctness to ad-hoc string conventions."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Replace `DockerData(string)` with explicit typed APIs (for example `DockerVolumesDir()` and `DockerBaseDir()`), and fail explicitly when runtime path discovery is unavailable.",
