        "dimension": "low_level_elegance",
        "related_files": [
          "goseg/docker/events/events.go",
          "goseg/broadcast/state.go",
          "goseg/docker/orchestration/subsystem/subsystem_events.go"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`publishDropOnFull` returns `ErrTransitionBusFull` via a non-blocking `default` case; events are dropped under transient backpressure.",
          "`PublishSchedulePack` in broadcast runtime also uses a non-blocking send with `errSchedulePackBusFull`.",
          "Docker subsystem listener returns an error when its event channel is saturated, turning pressure spikes into subsystem-level failures."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Define a shared backpressure policy (bounded wait with context, priority lanes for critical transitions, and overflow metrics) and apply it consistently across event and broadcast buses.",
