    "review::.::holistic::abstraction_fitness::runtime_bag_overreach::1a2657dc": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::abstraction_fitness::runtime_bag_overreach::1a2657dc",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 3,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "Runtime structs have grown into broad callback bags that obscure real domain boundaries and reduce abstraction leverage.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "abstraction_fitness",
        "related_files": [
          "goseg/startuporchestrator/startup_orchestrator.go",
          "goseg/importer/importer.go",
          "goseg/shipworkflow/operations_runtime.go",
          "goseg/docker/orchestration/runtime_ops.go",
          "goseg/main.go"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`startupInitRuntime` and `StartupRuntime` embed multiple grouped runtime structs plus many function seams, then compose long step lists with policy wrappers, indicating orchestration and dependency wiring are coupled in one abstraction.",
          "`importerRuntime` embeds storage/upload/provision groups and carries many callbacks (validation, filesystem, workflow, transition publishing), then aliases the same bag as init/workflow/publish runtime types.",
          "`workflowRuntime` embeds `RuntimeContainerOps`, `RuntimeUrbitOps`, and `RuntimeSnapshotOps` plus workflow-specific seams; this mixes unrelated concerns (container operations, DNS lookup, transition emission, upload orchestration) in one contract."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Split callback bags into narrower role-specific ports (e.g., `TransitionPublisher`, `ShipConfigStore`, `ContainerControl`, `StartupSubsystemRegistry`) and pass only the required role to each use case. Replace embedded mega-runtimes with constructor-wired services per workflow path.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
      "status": "open",
      "note": null,
      "first_seen": "2026-03-05T14:18:51+00:00",
      "last_seen": "2026-03-05T14:18:51+00:00",
      "resolved_at": null,
      "reopen_count": 0,
      "lang": "go",
      "suppressed": false,
      "suppressed_at": null,
      "suppression_pattern": null
    },
    "review::.::holistic::abstraction_fitness::withruntime_wrapper_chain_tax::b722131e": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::abstraction_fitness::withruntime_wrapper_chain_tax::b722131e",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 3,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "Repeated default/WithRuntime wrapper chains add call depth without adding policy or translation.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "abstraction_fitness",
        "related_files": [
          "goseg/broadcast/loop.go",
          "goseg/broadcast/state_lifecycle.go",
          "goseg/shipworkflow/operations_runtime.go",
          "goseg/routines/system/system.go",
          "goseg/main.go"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "Broadcast loop path layers through helper constructors and wrappers (`StartBroadcastLoop` -> `StartBroadcastLoopWithRuntime` -> `runBroadcastLoop` -> `runBroadcastTickWithRuntime`), while many wrappers only perform nil checks or default resolution.",
          "State lifecycle exposes near-duplicate runtime wrappers (`LoadStartramRegionsWithRuntime` forwarding to `LoadStartramRegionsWithRuntimeState`, plus similar runtime/default split for reload).",
          "Workflow and routine packages repeat this pattern (`DispatchUploadImport` -> `DispatchUploadImportWithCoordinator`; `StartBackupRoutines` forwarding to another package) with minimal abstraction gain."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Collapse wrapper layers into one explicit public path per use case: keep either default-only entrypoints or injected-runtime entrypoints, not both across all operations. Where both are required, enforce a single boundary adapter that adds concrete behavior (policy, telemetry, retries), not just forwarding.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
      "status": "open",
      "note": null,
      "first_seen": "2026-03-05T14:18:51+00:00",
      "last_seen": "2026-03-05T14:18:51+00:00",
      "resolved_at": null,
      "reopen_count": 0,
      "lang": "go",
      "suppressed": false,
      "suppressed_at": null,
      "suppression_pattern": null
    },
    "review::.::holistic::abstraction_fitness::zero_value_delegate_interface::b7416abd": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::abstraction_fitness::zero_value_delegate_interface::b7416abd",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 3,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "The event broker delegate abstraction duplicates the same contract with nearly pure pass-through methods.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "abstraction_fitness",
        "related_files": [
          "goseg/docker/events/events.go",
          "goseg/shipworkflow/operations_runtime.go",
          "goseg/importer/importer.go"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`DelegatingEventBroker` implements each `EventBroker` method by nil-checking and forwarding to `delegate` without adding cross-cutting behavior.",
          "Callers still capture concrete defaults (`events.DefaultEventRuntime()` in workflow and importer), so the delegation layer does not centralize policy or hide implementation changes.",
          "This creates another indirection surface while concrete publish semantics are already defined by `EventRuntime` + `publishDropOnFull`."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Remove `DelegatingEventBroker` unless it enforces real policy (e.g., tracing/metrics/retry/backpressure translation). If policy is needed, make that policy explicit in a single decorator used by runtime constructors and stop direct default-runtime capture in downstream packages.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
      "status": "open",
      "note": null,
      "first_seen": "2026-03-05T14:18:51+00:00",
      "last_seen": "2026-03-05T14:18:51+00:00",
      "resolved_at": null,
      "reopen_count": 0,
      "lang": "go",
      "suppressed": false,
      "suppressed_at": null,
      "suppression_pattern": null
    },
    "review::.::holistic::abstraction_fitness::mutable_global_runtime_singletons::465deb4f": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::abstraction_fitness::mutable_global_runtime_singletons::465deb4f",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 3,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "Mutable package-level default runtimes leak across boundaries and undermine explicit dependency abstractions.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "abstraction_fitness",
        "related_files": [
          "goseg/broadcast/state.go",
          "goseg/broadcast/loop.go",
          "goseg/docker/events/events.go"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "Broadcast state and loop maintain mutable globals with setters/resets (`DefaultBroadcastStateRuntime`, `SetDefaultBroadcastStateRuntime`, `defaultBroadcastLoopController`, `SetDefaultBroadcastLoopController`).",
          "Events runtime also exposes mutable process-global state (`defaultEventRuntime`, `SetDefaultEventRuntime`, `ResetDefaultEventRuntime`).",
          "This pattern allows hidden cross-module mutation and encourages callers to bypass explicit dependency injection, reducing interface honesty and making abstraction boundaries implicit."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Constrain mutable globals to bootstrap-only assembly and pass immutable runtime instances down from constructors. Deprecate public `SetDefault*` APIs in favor of context/service wiring so runtime ownership is explicit.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
      "status": "open",
      "note": null,
      "first_seen": "2026-03-05T14:18:51+00:00",
      "last_seen": "2026-03-05T14:18:51+00:00",
      "resolved_at": null,
      "reopen_count": 0,
      "lang": "go",
      "suppressed": false,
      "suppressed_at": null,
      "suppression_pattern": null
    },
    "review::.::holistic::cross_module_architecture::mixed_contract_ownership_boundary::3b427782": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::cross_module_architecture::mixed_contract_ownership_boundary::3b427782",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 3,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "Action contract governance mixes upload and c2c ownership domains while process-level quality gates are upload-centric, creating a boundary integrity gap.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "cross_module_architecture",
        "related_files": [
          "README.md",
          "goseg/protocol/contracts/catalog/action/specs.go",
          "goseg/protocol/contracts/conformance/fixtures_test.go"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "goseg/protocol/contracts/catalog/action/specs.go defines NamespaceUpload and NamespaceC2C contracts together, with OwnerUploadService and OwnerSystemWiFi respectively.",
          "README.md binds contract conformance gate to `./protocol/contracts/... ./uploadsvc/...`, which does not include the declared C2C runtime-owner module path.",
          "goseg/protocol/contracts/conformance/fixtures_test.go only asserts C2C fixture/catalog coherence, not owner-runtime behavior conformance."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Split governance into explicit per-owner contract families or add owner-scoped conformance suites and CI gates (e.g., include system/wifi owner runtime tests when c2c contracts exist). Keep contract catalog ownership and quality-gate scope mechanically aligned.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
