    "review::.::holistic::error_consistency::failfast_window_masks_delayed_startup_errors::361f02fd": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::error_consistency::failfast_window_masks_delayed_startup_errors::361f02fd",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 3,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "Fail-fast startup errors are only observed in a short window, then silently ignored.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "error_consistency",
        "related_files": [
          "goseg/startuporchestrator/startup_orchestrator.go",
          "goseg/startuporchestrator/startup_orchestrator_test.go",
          "goseg/main.go"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`waitForFailFastErrors` returns nil when its 250ms timeout expires even if fail-fast workers are still running and may fail later.",
          "`Bootstrap` invokes health once (`return o.health(ctx)`), so there is no ongoing reconciliation for delayed fail-fast worker errors during normal runtime.",
          "Tests validate near-immediate fail-fast errors (e.g., 20ms), but do not enforce behavior for failures after the timeout window."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Make fail-fast monitoring persistent: store terminal worker errors in shared state and have `health` report them without a fixed startup-only timeout; alternatively keep a supervisor goroutine that propagates late fail-fast errors to a shared fatal channel consumed by startup/runtime orchestration.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
      "status": "open",
      "note": null,
      "first_seen": "2026-03-05T14:18:51+00:00",
      "last_seen": "2026-03-05T14:18:51+00:00",
      "resolved_at": null,
      "reopen_count": 0,
      "lang": "go",
      "suppressed": false,
      "suppressed_at": null,
      "suppression_pattern": null
    },
    "review::.::holistic::error_consistency::wifi_partial_parse_hides_command_format_failures::22306509": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::error_consistency::wifi_partial_parse_hides_command_format_failures::22306509",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 3,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "Wi-Fi parsing tolerates malformed nmcli rows without surfacing partial-failure context.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "error_consistency",
        "related_files": [
          "goseg/system/wifi_runtime_methods.go",
          "goseg/system/wifi_runtime_api.go"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`parseNmcliWifiDeviceRecords` and `parseNmcliWifiScanResults` collect parse errors but only return an error when no valid rows were parsed.",
          "API calls like `ListWiFiSSIDs` treat parser success as fully valid output and return nil error, so malformed rows are silently dropped.",
          "This yields mixed semantics: severe parser issues are strict when output is empty, but non-strict when output is partially parseable, making failures harder to diagnose."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Introduce a typed partial-parse error (or warning payload) that includes dropped-row count and first parse cause; propagate it through `ListWiFiSSIDs`/device resolution so callers can distinguish clean success from degraded parsing.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
      "status": "open",
      "note": null,
      "first_seen": "2026-03-05T14:18:51+00:00",
      "last_seen": "2026-03-05T14:18:51+00:00",
      "resolved_at": null,
      "reopen_count": 0,
      "lang": "go",
      "suppressed": false,
      "suppressed_at": null,
      "suppression_pattern": null
    },
    "review::.::holistic::contract_coherence::stringly_typed_transition_event_contract::cdd8b0a1": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::contract_coherence::stringly_typed_transition_event_contract::cdd8b0a1",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 3,
      "confidence": "medium",
      "summary": "Transition event-type contracts are duplicated as string literals across workflow and importer paths.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "contract_coherence",
        "related_files": [
          "goseg/importer/importer.go",
          "goseg/shipworkflow/operations_runtime.go",
          "goseg/docker/events/events.go"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "Importer publish policy and constructors branch on literal type strings (`\"status\"`, `\"patp\"`, `\"extracted\"`, `\"error\"`).",
          "Workflow transition lifecycle emits the same semantic state using a hardcoded literal (`\"error\"`) in event planning.",
          "In parallel, event transport uses typed transition channels, so the type contract is not enforced uniformly end-to-end."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Define a shared typed transition-event vocabulary (constants or dedicated type with constructors) and replace ad-hoc string literals in importer/workflow publishers; keep compile-time checked conversions at transport boundaries.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
      "status": "open",
      "note": null,
